5. Privacy and Data
5.1 No Server-Side Data Collection

Pocketful is designed to run locally on your device:

We do not require you to create an account or sign in

We do not use Firebase, Supabase, or any analytics or tracking SDK

We do not collect or store your creative content or personal data on our servers

Please refer to our Privacy Policy for more details.

5.2 Device Permissions

The App may request access to:

Camera – to allow you to capture photos

Microphone – to allow you to record audio

Photo Library – to allow you to import existing images

These permissions are used solely to enable features within the App. You can manage these permissions in your device settings. If you disable a permission, the related feature may not work.

5.3 Data Loss

Because all data is stored locally on your device:

If you delete the App, all data stored within the App will be deleted and cannot be recovered by us

If your device is lost, damaged, or reset, we cannot recover your content

If you wish to keep your creations, please consider saving them outside of the App (for example, exporting or screenshotting them using your device’s system tools) before deleting the App or resetting your device.

